Beauty!

PAYTON is one of our very long term Cat Love Rescue residents who is currently in foster and we would truly love for her to finally find a home. Please open up your home to an older rescue cat in need who's been in the rescue system for way too long. 🐱❤️ Payton is a bit shy at first but once she gets to know you she will let you pet her (but she doesn't like to be picked up). She loves playing with other cats and does very well with others so she would be a purrrrfect cat to have around other cats if you have any. She loves running around after a laser light and likes playing with tennis balls! She also loves her wet food - yummy.

This sweetheart truly deserves to finally find a loving home to call her own. Please share her photo and story to help in finding her a home. You never know who might be looking to adopt. Thank you everyone.

If you would like to ADOPT Payton, or have any questions, please contact us. We would love to set up a meet and greet with you and Payton prior to an adoption so you can make sure she is the right cat for you. 😊

This week’s “happy tails” adoption story comes from Karen and Ryan who adopted lovabull Pittie, Hodor, this past summer! Follow his adventures on Instagram @hodorthepitbull 😍
“We may have chosen to meet Hodor out of his kennel, but really, he chose us when he decided to plop himself down in our laps and give us endless kisses. We instantly fell in love with his big head, gentle eyes, and goofy grin. The rest, as they say, is history. Our first month together was hard, as we dealt with a slew of medical issues from when Hodor was a stray.
Now that it's been almost 6 months, we can't imagine life without our big snuggle baby. We've learned that Hodor loves being outside, can't sleep without his blankie, thinks squirrels and cats are friends, and is a lapdog at heart. We're so happy we met Hodor at North Central. Our home has never been filled with more love and snuggles and dog hair, and we wouldn't have it any other way.”- Ryan & Karen
💗💗
Thank you for adopting and giving Hodor a loving family and for seeing him through his medical issues. He certainly looks like he’s settled in right at home! 😄
If you found your furry family member at North Central, send us your adoption story to share. Or if you’re looking to adopt or foster, please message us! 💌
-------------------------
North Central LA City shelter; 3201 Lacy St., Los Angeles, CA; 213-485-5767.

It's Merry Monday and little Merry is almost ready for a forever family. She will be spayed this week so after some time to heal she can go to her new home. Merry was rescued from a high kill shelter along with her 10 siblings and Mama Noel and has been in a loving foster home learning how to be a super sweet puppy. Some of her siblings look like Cattle dog mixes but Merry does not have those spots or markings so it is anyone's guess what her DNA could be. Her mama is a very pretty red color just like Merry, with more Lab or Golden features. In any case, Merry is adorable and loving and will be a wonderful addition to your family. Contact forgottenpetadvocates@yahoo.com to meet this baby.
